data.description:
As our lead developer, you will join our vibrant Medellin office, taking responsibility for developing our technical strategy and building a team that empowers our Experteering movement. While we have worked with technical teams before, we are largely non-technical, so communication with non-technical people is a must. Initially, you will work collaboratively with the entire MovingWorlds team, and most closely with Derk Norde who leads our product strategy. To support your work and our product, MovingWorlds has a technical advisor to help with onboarding, code review, and troubleshooting.

Our platform was developed in Node.js on a PostgreSQL database by various developers over the last 4 years. Over the past year, we have mostly worked with external contractors. As we are growing our team and programs, we're now looking to onboard a full-stack JavaScript web developer to our core team. As you will be the first technical person on the current team, we will look to you for creative and smart solutions, and there will be a clear growth opportunity for you to build a technical team around you.

In this role, you will drive the following key success indicators of the company through constant process and technology improvements:

● User experience scores of our platform, across all key stakeholders;
● Number of successful Experteering projects matched and completed;
● Reducing MovingWorlds program manager handling time per project match;
● Leveraging cutting-edge technology (e.g. matching algorithms, AI) to drive our business forward;
● Website uptime and performance.

If you feel this sounds like you, and you’re eager to join us to move worlds, apply now! Make sure your cover letter addresses the following:

1) Why you’d like to join MovingWorlds;
2) Why you're attracted by building this Experteering marketplace;
3) What’s the biggest strength you can bring to our team;
4) What you hope to learn;
5) Link to your any online coding profile(s). Also, feel free to indicate or attach any code that you’re particularly proud of.

For the first 6 months, you'd be working from our Medellin office in Colombia. After 6 months, your location may be more flexible and you might be partly location independent.

As we grow and add new members to our core team, we are intentionally offering a modest starting salary with an attractive equity package, as we want to invest in the growth opportunity in front of us. We plan to raise salaries for the entire team based on revenue targets in 2018.

